article.headline: Stetson 69, Kennesaw State 52
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- Sheldon Oliver scored 20 points to help Stetson defeat Kennesaw State 69-52 on Friday night and extend the Owls' losing streak to eight games. The Hatters (8-8, 5-3 Atlantic Sun Conference) used two second-half surges to rally from a first-half deficit. Stetson trailed by nine points with 2:57 left in the first half, then pulled within 31-25 at halftime. The Owls (5-10, 1-5) held a 35-27 advantage with 18:39 remaining, but failed to score for the next 6:19 as Stetson went on an 18-0 run. The Hatters next launched a 12-4 spurt to take a commanding 57-39 lead with 7:21 left. Stetson was 25-for-57 from the floor and 13-for-16 from the free-throw line while Kennesaw State made 21 of 57 field goals and 5 of 8 free throws. Garfield Blair added 15 points for Stetson and Tim Lang had 10. Kurtis Woods paced the Owls with 18 points.
